        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:35PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 235 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Prairie Point to near Boyd. Movement was
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Livingston, Boligee, Gainesville, Epes, Emelle, New West Greene,
Boyd, Panola, West Greene, The University Of West Alabama, Bluffport,
Tishabee, Geiger, Warsaw, New Mount Hebron, Sumterville, Clinton,
Pleasant Ridge, Five Points Intersection, and Payneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
